00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:16,368
you wanna do it right and not…
just throw it away,

312
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:19,288
that's why
you probably put pressure on yourself,

313
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:22,416
'cause you don't know
when you're gonna play again there.

314
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:24,084
It's how hard it is.

315
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:25,419
Polo's a hard sport,

316
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:29,882
{\an8}and everybody has to show up together
and click for there to be success.

317
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:34,094
There's a lot of things
that go into a successful team.

318
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:37,639
{\an8}These owners go out into the world,
they want the best athletes

319
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,476
that are gonna perform at their best.

320
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:43,854
So, you fall from that.

321
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:47,649
You don't become
a valuable player anymore for a team.

322
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:53,906
The future in Coca-Cola is no more future.
I mean, I'm not playing next year.

323
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:56,825
{\an8}

324
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:11,673
Polo is what
I want to do my whole life.

325
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:14,134
It's, uh, my only plan I have.

326
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,888
I didn't feel that it was my best season.

327
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:22,559
I didn't get to play…
what I know I can, or how I want to.

328
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:28,190
I mean, after you lost,
you're like, you cannot do anything there.

329
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:31,652
When I lose important games
or games that are tough,

330
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:32,611
I won't sleep.

331
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:37,574
I want that one.

332
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,162
Season's done.

333
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,165
Was it a stressful one, no?

334
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:50,295
I don't think it was fun.

335
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:55,008
We have to spend a lot of time together.

336
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:56,093
But why?

337
00:18:58,178 --> 00:19:01,682
For Keko and I,
I don't know what's going on.

338
00:19:01,765 --> 00:19:03,892
We say we're always going to be together,

339
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:07,271
and we're going to date forever,
and then end up together. It's hard.

340
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:12,442
Tensions and pressures,
during times like that, are pretty high.

341
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:16,238
Sometimes it's better
just to be alone, during the day,

342
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:17,656
and think about myself.

343
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:21,201
I felt Marissa understood it in some ways,
and in some other stuff

344
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:23,579
it must have been hard for her.

345
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:26,540
But it's what it was.

346
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:30,419
I'm dead.

347
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:33,547
You have so much more
to be happy about.

348
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:35,424
- Like what?
- With me.

349
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,429
Your girlfriend who you don't kiss.

350
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:52,983
{\an8}

351
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:58,280
When I was 20,
I could play a lot of games.

352
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:01,033
{\an8}But… today, uh,

353
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:04,077
{\an8}I need to take care of my body for sure.

354
00:20:04,661 --> 00:20:07,748
I try to do a little bit of this,
stretching.

355
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:10,209
If not, I can be really sore.

356
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:13,670
I couldn't start at the beginning
of the season like everybody else,

357
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:15,505
because I had a lower back injury.

358
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:20,510
And for me to come back from that,
to get to the semifinals, it's important.

359
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:22,971
Yes.

360
00:20:24,681 --> 00:20:29,728
I know that I can still compete against
these young, great kids that are coming.

361
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,605
This is better now.

362
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:34,483
So, I really hope we can make it
to the final of this Open,

363
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:36,860
because competing against Poroto

364
00:20:37,527 --> 00:20:40,530
makes me have this adrenaline again

365
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:43,325
of trying to get better
and compete and win.

366
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,536
But, first of all,

367
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:49,706
I have to beat his father, Adolfo.

368
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:55,379
He's an amazing polo player.

369
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:57,547
A lot of years
of playing against each other.

370
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,342
- <i>Facundo Pieres!</i>
- <i>Facundo!</i>

371
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:02,970
- <i>Cambiaso! Goal!</i>
- <i>Adolfo Cambiaso!</i>

372
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:07,140
Facundo Pieres and Adolfo
have been number one and number two

373
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:08,767
for the past 15 years.

374
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:11,853
Socially,
they high-five each other

375
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:15,357
and they're friends when
they're having asados, but on the field,

376
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:19,528
{\an8}as soon as a ball is hit, or a whistle,
